Blog.create(title: 'First Look at the Rumored Adidas UltraBOOST 2020', content: 'Although the hype surrounding adidas‘ UltraBOOST lineup has died down a bit since the silhouette’s inception, that hasn’t stopped the Germain giant in offering up new iterations of the beloved model.

After introducing the UltraBOOST ‘19 for this year, it looks as if a new version will soon be hitting the shelves. Shared via @sneakerprophet_, we have our first look at what could potentially be the UltraBOOST 2020. The sneaker seen above incorporates the same sleek design motif of the ‘19, however a few new details have been added such as the weave pattern on the Primeknit upper and taped Three Stripes cage. Additionally an iridescent “Metallic Purple” BOOST midsole finishes off the updated model. The pair also feature a co-branded tongue tab with ISS National Lab — a government-funded laboratory that aids in space research to improve life on Earth.

Keep it locked here for official imagery and a release date when they surface.

For sneakers you can purchase now, Stranger Things and Nike head back to the “Upside Down” in this week’s best footwear drops.
  ', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fadidas-ultraboost-2020-first-look-001.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')

Blog.create(title: 'Anthony Van Engelen Receives New Signature Sneaker: Vans AVE Pro', content: 'After recently showcasing its patchwork-clad “MONALISA” pack, Vans has returned with a new special silhouette that celebrates Anthony Van Engelen‘s skateboarding career: Vans AVE Pro. It’s been nearly 15 years since Engelen released a signature cupsole model, and this one is the most technically advanced one yet.

The signature sneaker blends classic fabrics with functional textiles, utilizing a mix of LuxLiner™ mesh overlays and premium suede. Putting together details like crisp white laces, tonal rubber eyelets and black side stripes, the silhouette offers a clean and modern exterior that hides a bevy of advanced materials like Duracap™ underlays and RapidWeld™ no-sew technology.

Below the mesh uppers, light grey suede panels sit at the forefoot and the heel for added traction against grip tape. All of these features sit atop the progressive UltimateWaffle cupsole, equipped with an internal shank that enables flexibility around the forefoot. Another layer of impact cushions and a full-length Ultracush midsole round up the features of the sole.

In the development of the shoe, Van Engelen worked with Vans’ design team every step of the way, testing and reiterating until they came up with something worthy of the his name. Van Engelen mentioned in a statement, “with the AVE Pro — my first cupsole in 15 years — we achieved a completely transformed upper with Vans’ Rapidweld technology and improved the grip and board-feel in the sole overall. This shoe for me was a natural progression toward making a durable, technical skate shoe. Not only does it deliver a lighter, longer-lasting shoe for skating—but it’s an important step in innovation for Vans to pursue as the leader in skate shoes.”

The Vans AVE Pro will be available worldwide on August 22 at vans.com.', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fvans-ave-pro-anthony-van-engelen-release-001.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')

Blog.create(title: 'A Closer Look at the UNDEFEATED x Nike Zoom Kobe 4 Protro Pack', content: 'To celebrate Kobe Bryant and all that is Mamba Day, UNDEFEATED and Nike have teamed up to release the Zoom Kobe 4 Protro Pack.

The range includes four different colorway options which presumably represent Team Kobe members DeMar DeRozan (“HYPER JADE”), Devin Booker (“TEAM ORANGE”), Kyle Kuzma (“COURT PURPLE”) and Giannis Antetokounmpo (“FIR”). “HYPER JADE” is decked out in teal with hits of orange; “TEAM ORANGE” is orange and purple; “COURT PURPLE” is purple and yellow; and finally “FIR” is green with white accents. Each model has been crafted from patent leather and features Kobe‘s soon-to-be-retired jersey numbers “8” and “24” debossed on the heels. UNDEFEATED’s Five Strikes logo comes in on the left tongue tab and can be seen in an iridescent shimmer printed on the lower back heels.

Each silhouette in the UNDEFEATED x Nike Zoom Kobe 4 Protro Pack will retail for $180 USD. The pack releases this Saturday, August 24 via raffle at each of UNDEFEATED’s chapter stores. Additionally a special range of co-branded basketball gear will also coincide with the sneaker release. An all-black basketball, shooting sleeves and duffle bag featuring iridescent Swoosh and Five Strike insignias, along with a mini basketball hoop and pump will be part of the lineup.

For more sneakers you can purchase now, Kanye serves up YEEZY 500s for the whole family in this week’s best footwear drops.
  ', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fundefeated-nike-zoom-kobe-4-protro-pack-better-look-release-info-013.jpg?q=80&w=1000&cbr=1&fit=max')

Blog.create(title: 'NikeCourt Celebrates the Big Apple With the Air Zoom Vapor X Kyrie 5 "NYC"', content: 'With the 2019 US Open right around the corner, NikeCourt recently put together an “NYC”-inspired colorway of the Air Zoom Vapor X Kyrie 5.

Revisiting the hybrid silhouette which mashes elements of tennis player Nick Kyrgios and basketball player Kyrie Irving‘s signature shoes, the latest take is centered around graffiti-inspired details. Dressed in a bold color scheme made up of purple and black, the New York homage sports vibrant volt midfoot Swooshes and “NYC” prints around the toe region. Additional details include torn-poster graphics on the toe bumpers and a marbled toe caps.

The NikeCourt Air Zoom Vapor X Kyrie 5 “NYC” is set to release globally on nike.com and select locations August 24.', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fnikecourt-air-zoom-vapor-x-kyrie-5-nyc-release-1.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')

Blog.create(title: 'Burberry Hiking Boot Gets Signature Check Update & Sturdy Rugged Soles', content: 'Fresh from the release of its check-covered low-top sneakers, Burberry has now dropped a pair of Brown Tor Vintage Check Hiking Boots as we gear up for Fall/Winter 2019.

The Riccardo Tisci-designed boots feature a mixture of checkered cloth, suede, leather and rubber panels on its upper. Tanned brown leather is used to construct the supportive areas such as the toe box and heel section, while darker brown suede is used for the vamp and forefoot. The archetype check design is used for the mid-panel, and a contrasting touch of black perforated leather has been added around the collar.

Burberry’s hiking boot is covered in premium details such as metal lace loops and rivets lining the tongue — which sports a rubberized Burberry plaque at the top — while the recently introduced “TB” Thomas Burberry logo has been added to the rear-quarter at the heel in white for more contrasting elements. The boot sits atop a chunky rubber sole unit, which also features “TB” and Burberry branding, and is finished with a hiking rope lace system and a yellow leather lining.

You can pick up a pair of the Burberry Tor Vintage Check Hiking Boots from retailers such as Browns now for $890 USD.', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fburberry-brown-tor-vintage-check-hiking-boots-release-information-1.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')
Blog.create(title: 'size? and Vans Stitch Together Third Patchwork Sneaker Collaboration', content: 'Though size? has kept busy with frequent adidas collaborations, its joint efforts with Vans remain longstanding fan favorites. Thus, sneakerheads should rejoice at the news that the Manchester-based boutique has rejoined the California-based sneaker brand for “Patchwork III,” the pair’s third mismatched silhouette.

This time, the Bold Ni is the model of choice, sporting a monochrome patchwork makeover that highlights its asymmetric detailing. Like the Old Skool “Factory Floor,” size?’s latest collaborative silhouette takes cues from excess scraps found throughout Vans’ Anaheim factory.

Over a dozen different textiles appear across the sleek shoe, intentionally mismatching the various pony hair, checkerboard, camo, polka dots, denim and suede seen throughout. Uneven foxing tape and touches of transparent TPU keep the dynamic design feeling fresh, with an UltraCush Lite sockliner for heightened comfort.

Expect the collaborative Vans Bold Ni silhouette to hit size?’s web store and app on August 30.', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fsize-vans-bold-ni-patchwork-black-white-asymmetric-collab1.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')
Blog.create(title: 'A Closer Look at FILA''s Disruptor 2 "Zebra" and Nike''s "Crimson/Gold" Air Max 200', content: 'As the latest additions to Bloomingdale’s impressive selection of sneakers, the FILA Disruptor 2 Premium “Zebra” and Nike Air Max 200 cater to footwear enthusiasts with bold personal style. With their graphic yet distinct details, the offerings represent the breadth of noteworthy shoes available from the retailer.

The Nike Air Max 200 is the newest member of the Air Max family, notable for its visible air and updated cushioning. Though the midsole and heel bubble are similar to the Air Max 180, a reimagined upper sets the shoe apart from its predecessors. On this version, the black and white upper is brightened with hits of layered suede panels in “Bright Crimson,” “University Gold” and green, as well as a gradient Air 200 logo on the tongue.

For its exclusive women’s offerings, Bloomingdale’s adds the FILA Disruptor 2 Premium, reimagined in a zebra print pony hair — a bold update to the brand’s already popular chunky-soled silhouette. Having originally been released in 1996, the model has re-established itself as a wardrobe staple in the contemporary. Rounding out the shoe is its signature sawtooth rubber outsole and the FILA logo hitting the shoe’s tongue, quarter, midsole and back counter.', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fbloomingdales-fila-disruptor-zebra-nike-slam-dunk-vandalised-4.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')
Blog.create(title: 'AFEW & Diadora''s N.9000 "Highly Addictive" Will Be Limited to Just 50 Pairs', content: 'AFEW and Diadora are coming together once again for the release of the N.9000 “Highly Addictive.” The highly-limited pair pays homage to 2017’s V.7000 “Highly Addictive,” a pair that is highly sought-after on the resell market nowadays.

The N.9000 iteration by AFEW and Diadora sports the same light green, pale red and off-white color scheme as the V.7000, and is made from premium kangaroo leather upper in Italy. AFEW, “NYC,” “DUS” and Diadora branding in tonal colors decorate the sneaker’s immaculate upper, which draws inspiration from New York City’s heavy use of raw concrete for darker overlaying sections.

Attention to detail was key in the making of this rare sneaker, as AFEW and Diadora round off the design with a leather lining, pill-printed insoles and beautifully supple leather throughout. Embroidered tongues sport the Diadora moniker, while the heel tabs are given laser-etched pill motifs taken from the V.7000.

The AFEW x Diadora N.9000 “Highly Addictive” will be limited to just 50 units — similar to the Friends and Family V.7000 — and will be sold exclusively in-store at Sneakersnstuff New York for $230 USD on September 7. Take a closer look at the highly-anticipated pair above.', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fafew-diadora-highly-addictive-n-9000-sneaker-release-information-sneakersnstuff-nyc-1.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')
Blog.create(title: 'Liam Gallagher & adidas Spezial Unveil Minimalistic Padiham LG SPZL', content: 'adidas Originals and Liam Gallagher have debuted their upcoming collaborative Spezial silhouette, the Padiham LG SPZL.

The minimalist sneaker will release alongside Gallagher’s upcoming album, Why Me? Why Not?, and was previously spotted on foot of the former Oasis frontman at an exclusive gig in London back in June. Today, adidas Originals offers a first look at the duo’s offering, which sports a clean cream suede and leather upper alongside a matching low-profile sole unit.

Gallagher and the Spezial team drew inspiration from the original Padiham SPZL, a silhouette inspired by a vintage adidas style unearthed by Gary Aspden. Using this as a base, the team made the sneaker more neutral and understated. Other features of the design include gold foil branding, a zig-zag cut eyestay, zig-zag leather Three Stripes, and a gum sole unit finished in cream. To rework the original Padiham SPZL’s design, a new tongue featuring Liam Gallagher’s face and dual branding has also been added.

The collaborative pair is a nod to Liam Gallagher’s affinity for adidas, which he wore “religiously” when growing up. Gallagher says that the collaboration with Spezial came about because he “wears the clobber and it’s cool like me.”

Gary Aspden says, “I have known Liam for over 20 years and we have always got on. He is one of the people who have worn and supported what we do with adidas Spezial since day one so this collaboration evolved organically.”

Aspden added, “We made a few tweaks to the upper pattern along with a different tongue — as anyone who is a fan of gum soled, suede adidas trainers, knows it is all about those subtle details. Liam gave comments on each sample until the final version which we held off on showing him until we presented them to him for the first time backstage at his gig in Hackney. We filmed that moment as we wanted to capture his honest reaction. Anyone who has worn the Three Stripes loyally for as long as he has will understand that excitement.”

Pick up a pair of the limited-edition Liam Gallagher x adidas Spezial Padiham LG SPZL at adidas Originals stores and online on August 30.', image_url: 'https://image-cdn.hypb.st/https%3A%2F%2Fhypebeast.com%2Fimage%2F2019%2F08%2Fadidas-originals-spezial-liam-gallagher-padiham-lg-spzl-release-information-1.jpg?q=90&w=1400&cbr=1&fit=max')